{{advert|date=December 2017}} {{Primary Sources|date=December 2017}}
{{Infobox Bibliographic Database |name =Indian Citation Index |image = |caption = |producer = Diva Enterprises Pvt. Ltd. |country = INDIA |providers =Various Universities, Institutions and Commercial organizations |cost = Yes |disciplines =Multidisciplinary |depth =Citation indexing, Author, Topic title, Subject keywords, Abstract, Periodical title, Author's address, Publication year |formats =Research, Reviews, Editorials, Short communication, Research note, Case study, Research method, Opinion papers, Observations (R&D), Special articles, Patent, Standard, Report (R&D), Proceedings papers |temporal =2004 to present |geospatial =Indian |number = 600 thousand indexed articles and 11.5 million references |updates = |p_title = |p_dates = |ISSN = |web =http://www.indiancitationindex.com/ |titles = }}
The [[Indian Citation Index (ICI)]] is an online [[bibliographic database]] containing [[abstract (summary)|abstract]]s and [[citation]]s from [[academic journals]]. Currently ICI covers more than 1000+ [[Academic journal|journal]]s from India covering [[scientific]], [[Technology|technical]], [[medical]], and [[social sciences]] that includes [[arts]] and [[humanities]]. ICI covers data from 2004 onwards and provides full text of the title for [[Open Access]] journals, at present there are more than 280+ OA journals. ICI provides search and analytical features. ICI was launched in India in 2009 and is funded by Diva Enterprises Pvt. Ltd.. <ref name="ICI">http://www.indiancitationindex.com</ref>
==Overview== The ICI was launched in Oct 2009 New Delhi, with 100 journals. It provides access to [[full text]] for all [[Open Access]] journals. It links to [[Google Scholar]] for additional information and provides analytical tools.
There are 50 different top level subject categories like [[Health Science]], [[Mathematics]], [[Computer Science]] & [[Technology]], [[Economics]], and [[Agriculture]]. These subject categories are further sub-divided into second and third level.
==Coverage== The database is constantly updated, nearly two/three [[Academic journal|journal]]s are added every month, target is to add 1000 [[Academic journal|journal]]s.
Details about ICI database * 1000+ [[Science]], [[Technology|technical]], [[medical]], and [[social sciences]] (including [[arts]] and [[humanities]]) * 280+ [[Open Access]] [[Academic journal|journal]]s, ICI provides [[full text]] for these [[Academic journal|journal]]s * Coverage from 2004 to present day * 600+ thousand source titles (index [[article (publishing)|article]]s) * 11.5+<ref name="ICI" /> million references
==See also== * [[Energy Science and Technology Database]] * [[ETDEWEB]] * [[Geographic Names Information System]] * [[Global Health database]] * [[Materials Science Citation Index]] * [[List of academic journal search engines]]
