{{infobox Museum |name= Museo de la Exploración Rudolph Amandus Philippi |image= Museo Rodulfo A. Philippi.JPG |imagesize= 260px |map_type = |map_caption = |latitude = |longitude = |established= 2006 |location= Avenida Los Laureles, [[Isla Teja]], [[Valdivia, Chile|Valdivia]] |visitors= |director= Karin Weil |publictransit = |website= [http://www.uach.cl/direccion/museologica/m_pe_historia.htm Museo de la Exploración Rudolph Amandus Philippi] }} '''Museo de la Exploración Rudolph Amandus Philippi''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for ''Museum of the Exploration Rudolph Amandus Philippi'') is a [[museum]] in [[Valdivia, Chile|Valdivia]] run by [[Universidad Austral de Chile]]. The exhibitions at the museum deals with the exploration of southern Chile, specially those made by the [[Germans|German]] [[naturalist]] [[Rudolph Amandus Philippi]].
