[[Image:Good.Shepherd.Vatican.Museum.jpg|thumb|160px|The [[Good Shepherd]], c. 300 at the Pio Cristiano Museum, Rome]]

The '''Pio Cristiano Museum''' is one of the [[Vatican Museums]]. It houses various works of Christian antiquity.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.museivaticani.va/content/museivaticani/en/collezioni/musei/museo-pio-cristiano.html|title=Pius-Christian Museum - Vatican Museums|website=www.museivaticani.va|language=en|access-date=2018-05-07}}</ref>

The museum was founded by Pope [[Pius IX]] in 1854,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vaticanstate.va/content/vaticanstate/en/monumenti/musei-vaticani/museo-pio-cristiano.paginate.1.html|title=Pio-Christian Museum|website=www.vaticanstate.va|access-date=2018-05-07}}</ref> two years after the establishment of the [[Pontifical Commission for Sacred Archaeology]].

