The '''Slovenian Albums Chart''' SLO Top 30 is the official chart of music albums based on sales in [[Slovenia]]. The chart composes national as well as international music albums and compilations. The highest grossing album of 2012 was [[21 (Adele album)|21]] by [[Adele]]. The SLO Top 30 Chart is the only official music chart in Slovenia based on sales. Due to Slovenia's small market, the country does not have its own official Singles Chart, but has a variety of Radio Charts and Playlist Charts. The SLO Top 30 is updated weekly, on Thursdays on http://www.val202.si/slotop30/, as well as on the [[Val 202]] Radio and Vikend magazine on Fridays.

[[Category:Slovenian music]]
[[Category:Record charts]]

'''The Chronicle of King Henry VIII. of England''', commonly known as the '''Spanish Chronicle''' is a [[chronicle]] written during the reigns of [[Henry VIII of England|Henry VIII]] and [[Edward VI of England|Edward VI]] by an unknown author.

The chronicle was translated from [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and published with notes in 1889, by the respected historian, [[Martin Hume]].<ref>{{cite NIE |title=Hume, Martin Andrew Sharp |volume=X |page=310 |url=https://archive.org/stream/newinternational10gilm#page/310/mode/2up }}</ref> Hume appears to have regarded the work as an authentic contemporary document from the 16th century that related an eyewitness' account of various events in the Tudor period. [[Alison Weir]], in ''[[The Six Wives of Henry VIII (book)|The Six Wives of Henry VIII]]'', notes that the Spanish Chronicle is "notoriously inaccurate".{{sfn|Weir|2008|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=M1yHXitDdyQC&pg=315#v=onepage&q&f=false 315]}}   

